## `ctx.ui.setWidget` constraints

- `render(width): string[]` lines must have visible width `<= width`.
- ANSI ok, but never use `.slice()` on styled strings.
- Use:
  - `visibleWidth(str)` for display cells
  - `truncateToWidth(str, width, "")` for ANSI-safe clipping
  - `wrapTextWithAnsi(str, width)` for wrapped styled text
- TUI resets SGR/OSC8 at end of every line → reapply style per line.
- `string[]` direct widgets get wrapped in `Text(line, 1, 0)` and Pi caps to `MAX_WIDGET_LINES = 10`.
- Component/factory widgets are better here: render gets current `width`, can truncate precisely.
- Widget placement default = `"aboveEditor"`. Can be explicit:
  ```ts
  ctx.ui.setWidget(PANEL_KEY, factory, { placement: "aboveEditor" });
  ```

## Update frequency

- `render()` must be sync + cheap. No git calls inside.
- Keep current debounce (`REFRESH_DEBOUNCE_MS = 1000`) good.
- Set widget once, hold `tui.requestRender()` handle, mutate shared state, request render.
- Don’t call `setWidget()` every refresh unless mounting/unmounting.
- Hide when no files:
  ```ts
  ctx.ui.setWidget(PANEL_KEY, undefined);
  ```

## Cleanup

- On no changes / disabled / shutdown:
  ```ts
  ctx.ui.setWidget(PANEL_KEY, undefined);
  ```
- Pi disposes existing widget when same key replaced/removed.
- If widget has timers/listeners, expose `dispose()`.
- Clear refresh timer on `session_shutdown`.

## Adapt design

Use `renderPanel(state, theme, width, height)` full-width above input. Pick height inside widget because widget render gets no height.

Recommended:
- `height = min(10, max(4, files.length + 4))`
- render only when `state.enabled && state.files.length > 0`
- keep status line always optional
- remove `CustomEditor` replacement
- scroll commands still mutate `state.scrollOffset` + request widget render

Core widget factory:

```ts
let widgetHandle: { requestRender: () => void } | undefined;
let widgetMounted = false;

const syncWidget = (ctx: ExtensionContext) => {
	if (!ctx.hasUI) return;

	const shouldShow = state.enabled && state.files.length > 0 && !state.error;

	if (!shouldShow) {
		if (widgetMounted) {
			ctx.ui.setWidget(PANEL_KEY, undefined);
			widgetMounted = false;
			widgetHandle = undefined;
		}
		return;
	}

	if (!widgetMounted) {
		ctx.ui.setWidget(
			PANEL_KEY,
			(tui, theme) => {
				widgetHandle = { requestRender: () => tui.requestRender() };

				return {
					render(width: number): string[] {
						if (width < 20) return [];
						const height = Math.min(10, Math.max(4, state.files.length + 4));
						return renderPanel(state, theme, width, height)
							.slice(0, height)
							.map((line) => truncateToWidth(line, width, ""));
					},
					invalidate(): void {},
					dispose(): void {
						widgetHandle = undefined;
					},
				};
			},
			{ placement: "aboveEditor" },
		);
		widgetMounted = true;
	} else {
		widgetHandle?.requestRender();
	}
};
```

Then after refresh:

```ts
finally {
	refreshInFlight = false;
	updateStatus(ctx);
	syncWidget(ctx);
}
```

Scroll commands:

```ts
const requestWidgetRender = () => widgetHandle?.requestRender();

pi.registerCommand("diff-panel-up", {
	description: "Scroll the git diff widget up",
	handler: async () => {
		state.scrollOffset = Math.max(0, state.scrollOffset - 1);
		requestWidgetRender();
	},
});

pi.registerCommand("diff-panel-down", {
	description: "Scroll the git diff widget down",
	handler: async () => {
		state.scrollOffset += 1;
		requestWidgetRender();
	},
});
```

Shutdown cleanup:

```ts
pi.on("session_shutdown", async (_event, ctx) => {
	if (refreshTimer) clearTimeout(refreshTimer);
	if (ctx.hasUI) {
		ctx.ui.setWidget(PANEL_KEY, undefined);
		ctx.ui.setStatus(STATUS_KEY, undefined);
	}
	widgetMounted = false;
	widgetHandle = undefined;
});
```

